      "note": "I.e., \"you did not have to fight for it, since the enemy surrendered without giving battle\". The term fay' (a noun derived from the verb fa'a, \"he returned [something]\" or \"turned [it] over\") is applied in the Qur'an and the Traditions exclusively to war-gains - whether consisting of lands, or tribute, or indemnities - which are obtained, as a condition of peace, from an enemy who has laid down arms before actual fighting has taken place (Taj al-'Arus)."
